cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with learning factorized symbolic representations from visual data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves a neural network architecture and learning algorithm, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions using the approach on Atari 2600 games, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) to some extent.
